The manuscript operates in three distinct registers that are appropriately deployed:

**Register 1 — Literary-Academic Hybrid** (Chapters 1–3, Epilogue)  
Elise Chen's perspective: precise scientific observation filtered through character consciousness. Strong. No tone drift.

**Register 2 — Sociological Field Notes** (Chapters 16–17)  
Dante Reyes' perspective: street-level, interview-rich, deliberately vernacular. The DMV analogy ("it sure acts like it has priorities") is exactly the right register for this material.

**Register 3 — Policy-Technical** (Chapters 18–23)  
Formal equation specification, call to action, research agenda. Clean, authoritative, appropriately assertive without being strident.

